<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF776AC8FF579E151B5EB38E" pageId="140" pageNumber="900" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF776AC8FF579E151B5EB38E" blockId="140.[169,1377,1453,2316]" pageId="140" pageNumber="900">
<emphasis id="F6E0EAECFF776AC8FF579E151C07B35F" bold="true" box="[171,519,2124,2157]" pageId="140" pageNumber="900">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Least Concern on The IUCN Red List. Full extent of the distribution of the 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF776AC8FDF69E2A1CBDB3A6" authority="Woolly" authorityName="Woolly" box="[522,701,2163,2196]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Kerivoula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="140" pageNumber="900" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lenis">Lenis Woolly</taxonomicName>
Bat is uncertain, but it is no doubt wide but fragmentary. Additional studies are needed to clarify its taxonomy and conservation status.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
